==French==
===Etymology===
Latin [[visitare]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/vizite/}}

===Verb===
'''visiter''' 

# to [[visit]] (a place)
#:''Tu dois visiter Paris un jour.''
#::''You must visit Paris one day''

====Usage note====
''Visiter'' is only used for places. In French they say "rendre visite à" for people, i.e. "Je rendre visite à mon père à Paris.'' = ''I'm visitting my father in Paris.''

